2. cs.CY (Computers and Society): Mental health is a societal issue, and this paper focuses on using natural language processing to improve mental health counseling. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to this sub-category.

3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The study involves analyzing text-message-based counseling conversations, which can be considered a form of social network. Therefore, this sub-category is also a possibility.

4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses actionable conversation strategies that are associated with better conversation outcomes, which can be relevant to the field of human-computer interaction. Therefore, this sub-category is also a possibility.

5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper involves the development of computational methods to analyze counseling conversations, which can be considered a form of machine learning. Therefore, this sub-category is also a possibility.
